{{notability|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Religion and Violence | cover = [[File:jrv_new-cover.gif]] | editor = Margo S. Kitts | discipline = [[Religious studies]], [[theology]] | formernames = | abbreviation = J. Religion Violence | publisher = [[Philosophy Documentation Center]] | country = | frequency = Triannual | history = 2013-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = https://www.pdcnet.org/jrv | link2 = https://www.pdcnet.org/jrv/toc | link2-name = Online access | JSTOR = | OCLC = 699807153 | LCCN = 2011201815 | CODEN = | ISSN = | eISSN = 2159-6808 }} The '''''Journal of Religion and Violence''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering the study of [[religion]] and [[violence]]. It publishes analyses of contemporary and historical religious groups involved in violent incidents, as well as studies on sacrifice, terrorism, inter- and intra-religious violence, mass suicide, war and religion, and religiously-legitimated violence against women. It also publishes reviews and special issues dedicated to relevant topics.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pdcnet.org/jrv/Special-Issues | title=Special Issue list, ''Journal of Religion and Violence'' |accessdate=1 May 2018}}</ref> The journal is indexed in the [[ATLA Religion Database]] and [[ERIH PLUS]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dbh.nsd.uib.no/publiseringskanaler/erihplus/periodical/info.action?id=480633 | title=ERIHPLUS web site |accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref> and has a Level 1 classification from the Publication Forum of the Federation of Finnish Learned Societies.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.julkaisufoorumi.fi/en | title=Publication Forum web site |accessdate=25 April 2018}}</ref> The ''Journal of Religion and Violence'' is a [[hybrid open-access journal]] with a [[SHERPA/RoMEO]] "green" self-archiving policy.<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://www.sherpa.ac.uk/romeo/issn/2159-6808/ | title=SHERPA/RoMEO web site |accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> It is published by the [[Philosophy Documentation Center]]<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.pdcnet.org/jrv | title=Philosophy Documentation Center web site |accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>
